<div id="review_1259978372" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1259978372" />
    <a title="Jonathan K" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32433113-jonathan-k"><img alt="Jonathan K" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1404758116p2/32433113.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1259978372?book_show_action=true">Jun 11, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jonathan K" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jonathan K" href="/user/show/32433113-jonathan-k">Jonathan K</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1259978372" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer861456375422003323">Having recently read &quot;Lonesome Dove&quot; I realized it had been many years since I&apos;d first read this book. A film buff the Oscar winning movie is memorable, especially Shirley McClain&apos;s characterization of Aurora Greenwood, one of the most unique characters every created by any author. I&apos;d forgotten the character Jack Nicholson plays in the film isn&apos;t originally in the book, though the trio of Aurora&apos;s suitors are just as quirky and would love to have seen them in the film. Regardless Larry shows wh</span>
  <span id="freeText861456375422003323" style="display:none">Having recently read "Lonesome Dove" I realized it had been many years since I'd first read this book. A film buff the Oscar winning movie is memorable, especially Shirley McClain's characterization of Aurora Greenwood, one of the most unique characters every created by any author. I'd forgotten the character Jack Nicholson plays in the film isn't originally in the book, though the trio of Aurora's suitors are just as quirky and would love to have seen them in the film. Regardless Larry shows what a master storyteller he is here, much as he has with other books. His characters are unique, and what plays out keeps the reader engaged. Aurora is quite the character in all respects and you can't help laugh when reading her dialog; 'a real piece of work' comes to mind. Highly recommended in all respects! </span>
  <a data-text-id="861456375422003323" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
