<div id="review_66767601" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/66767601" />
    <a title="Lori Anderson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/382208-lori-anderson"><img alt="Lori Anderson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1606790681p2/382208.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/66767601?book_show_action=true">Aug 09, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lori Anderson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lori Anderson" href="/user/show/382208-lori-anderson">Lori Anderson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780684853901" href="/book/show/317843.Terms_of_Endearment">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">no one</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer66767601&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer66767601" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1374630672820304237">*** SPOILER ALERT ***<br/><br/>I saw this movie when was I was about 15 years old and some idiot woman in ALL her wisdom thought it would be the PERFECT movie for bunch of middle school and teenagers to watch during a church lock-in. All it did was confuse the middle-schoolers and resort me to tears. NOT an appropriate movie at all.<br/><br/>I finally got around to reading the book this week. I have read several of Larry McMurtry&apos;s novels and have always appreciated his dry wit, so I was hoping the book would be mu</span>
  <span id="freeText1374630672820304237" style="display:none">*** SPOILER ALERT ***<br /><br />I saw this movie when was I was about 15 years old and some idiot woman in ALL her wisdom thought it would be the PERFECT movie for bunch of middle school and teenagers to watch during a church lock-in. All it did was confuse the middle-schoolers and resort me to tears. NOT an appropriate movie at all.<br /><br />I finally got around to reading the book this week. I have read several of Larry McMurtry's novels and have always appreciated his dry wit, so I was hoping the book would be much better than the movie. <br /><br />Ah, well. I can sum it up this way. WAY too much Aurora, far too little Emma. I started getting so bored with Aurora that I began skimming pages. I would have loved to have seen Emma fleshed out a bit more, but maybe that says it all about Emma -- Aurora overshadowed her so much in her life that she was relegated to little more than a foot note.<br /><br />And Flap should be slapped. He is just foul in my opinion. I couldn't stand him.<br /><br />I gave the book three stars because there were some humorous spots in the movie. The bit about Royce driving his truck through the bar and all over the dance floor looking for his wife was wryly hysterical. But I wouldn't waste my time reading this again, or recommending it.<br /><br />Lori Anderson<br /><br /><a href="http://www.lorianderson.net" rel="nofollow noopener">Lori Anderson:The Store</a> <br /><a href="http://www.lorianderson.blogspot.com" rel="nofollow noopener">Pretty Things:The Blog</a> <br /><a href="http://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=1152557235&amp;ref=profile" rel="nofollow noopener">Facebook</a><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1374630672820304237" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


