              <span id="reviewTextContainer1846031796" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15788234059938473031">With the death of this great author, I figured I’d pick one of his to read next. I had already read the Lonesome Dove series, Berrybender Tales, and the first two of The Last Picture Show series. So ToE seemed appropriate for next on the list.<br/><br/>Not my kind of book at all, but McMurtry is such a good writer he keeps you laughing, interested, and turning pages. <br/><br/>Great characters who are both deeply flawed and in some way likable.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


